---
title: Spicy Miso Rigatoni With Bacon plus Caramelized Shallot, Zucchini & Parmesan
description: Bacon makes everything better! It boosts other umami-rich ingredients like miso and Parmesan for this irresistible fusion dish. The bacon joins zucchini and shallot in a savory sauce flavored with garlic and Sriracha and swirled with butter and sour cream for a luxuriously creamy pasta bowl that’s sure to be an instant hit—all in just 30 minutes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66f2d7231e86f3e65846f9ef-14b62af8.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66f31e641e86f3e65847016b-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spicy-miso-rigatoni-with-bacon-66f31e641e86f3e65847016b
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 850 kcal
  fat: 47 g
  saturated fat: 21 g
  carbohydrates: 82 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 26 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1490 mg
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
cuisine: East Asia
time required: 25 minutes
---

Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil.

Heat a large dry #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%oz}; cook,
turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until
crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.
Carefully discard all but a thin layer of bacon fat from pan.

Once bacon is cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

While bacon cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved) lengthwise; slice crosswise into
1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@shallot{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced). Trim and thinly slice
@scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Once water is boiling, add @rigatoni pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}; drain.

Once pasta has cooked 4 minutes, return pan with bacon fat to stovetop over
medium-high heat. (TIP: If pan seems dry, add a drizzle of @?oil{}.) Add
zucchini, shallot, and scallion whites; cook, stirring frequently, until
browned and tender, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Add @miso sauce concentrate{2%units}, @pork ramen stock concentrate{1%unit},
@garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the @Sriracha sauce{1%tsp}, @cold water{1/2%cup},
and a pinch of @sugar{pinch} to pan with veggies (all the Sriracha and
@cold water{3/4%cup} for 4 servings). Stir to combine. Bring to a simmer,
stirring occasionally.

Once sauce is simmering, add drained rigatoni and half the bacon. Cook, tossing,
until pasta is evenly coated, ~{1-3%minutes}. TIP: If sauce seems too thick,
add water 1 TBSP at a time.

Turn off heat; stir in @sour cream{3%tbsp} and @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4).
Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Divide pasta between bowls; top with @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}, scallion greens,
and remaining bacon. Serve.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

> Butter and sour cream create a luxuriously creamy pasta bowl that's sure to
be an instant hit—all in just 30 minutes.